:INFO
The Novel That Broke My Sleep Schedule
I started Recursion on a Sunday evening thinking I would read one chapter. By \
midnight I had read 200 pages and given up on sleeping at a reasonable hour. \
Blake Crouch builds a premise about memory and time that escalates so quickly \
and so relentlessly that stopping feels physically difficult. I have read several \
thrillers that claim to be impossible to put down. This one actually was.

:COUNTER.half
342 Pages
